<subSubSection id="C3485ED60941B21CEC95FCBA21364B4F" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="473" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0941B21FEC95FCBA22BA498D" blockId="21.[151,1437,870,1077]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEC95FCBA212949A9" bold="true" box="[151,290,870,896]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FED2AFCBB216549A8" box="[296,366,871,897]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FED2AFCBB216549A8" box="[296,366,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: named based on a vernacular Indian name, a fish living in mud; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE83CFCBA247649A9" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[1086,1149,870,896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sharq">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE83CFCBA247649A9" box="[1086,1149,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">sharq</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the Arabic word for east, for its distribution range in north-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0941B21FEE67FC5622A6498D" box="[613,685,906,932]" name="Oman" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Oman</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
