<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FECC5F86C21AA4DE3" bold="true" box="[199,417,1968,1994]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Short description:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEDAAF86D223E4DE3" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[424,565,1968,1995]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sharq">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEDAAF86D223E4DE3" box="[424,565,1968,1995]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra sharq</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is differentiated from the other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FE811F86D24524DE2" box="[1043,1113,1969,1995]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FE811F86D24524DE2" box="[1043,1113,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Garra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Hajar Mountains e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0941B21FEC95F809213F4DC7" authorityName="Fowler &amp; Steinitz" authorityYear="1956" box="[151,308,2004,2031]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barreimiae">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0941B21FEC95F809213F4DC7" box="[151,308,2004,2031]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">G. barreimiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of orange spot at the upper opercle (vs. presence) and a white dorsal fin tip (vs. presence), and by having 10–14 gill rakers on the lower limb of the first gill arch (vs. 15–18). It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0942B21CE94FFF4B20E34AFC" authorityName="Krupp" authorityYear="1988" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gallagheri">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0942B21CE94FFF4B20E34AFC" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">G. gallagheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0942B21CED1DFF6721B44AFC" box="[287,447,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipinnis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0942B21CED1DFF6721B44AFC" box="[287,447,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">G. longipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a strongly mottled flank pattern (vs. almost plain or with slight mottling) and individual or series of orange midlateral flank scales (vs. no orange scales). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0942B21CEFF4FF0324884AD0" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" box="[1014,1155,223,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sharq">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0942B21CEFF4FF0324884AD0" box="[1014,1155,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Garra sharq</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0942B21CE983FF0320E34B34" authorityName="Kirchner, Kruckenhauser, Pichler, Borkenhagen &amp; Freyhof" authorityYear="2020" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Garra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shamal">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0942B21CE983FF0320E34B34" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">G. shamal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of a white dorsal-fin tip (vs. presence), orange scales on the flank usually present (vs. usually absent) and having black dorsal-fin membranes (vs. hyaline, brown, grey, often hyaline in proximal and black on distal portion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
